Author: Leonidas S. Barbosa (alias: Kirotawa)
E-mail: kirotawa[put a sign here]gmail[a dot here]com
Version: 0.18.08.11 (octopus-ink)

Description: GmailCommandLine is a simple app to send e-mail via a  gmail account on unix bash. It was built to send emails faster no be necessary to open your gmail account in browser.

New features: can use many e-mails with '@gmail', just put your new address or select it in the list
    Example:
            1 kirotawa@gmail.com
            2 kirotawa2@gmail.com
            3 kirotawa3@gmail.com
            Choose a address : 

Uage: gmailcommandline.py [options]

Options:
  -h, --help            Show the help message.
  -d DESTINATION, --destination=DESTINATION
                        Sets a destination address to send email, otherwise send to default, yourself email.
  -a ATTACH, --attachpath=ATTACH
                        Attach  a file to email.
  -m "MESSAGE", --message="MESSAGE"
                        Content of message that you want to send. Use quotes to set the message.
  -u USERMAIL, --usermail=USERMAIL
                        You user email of Gmail. Just need set
                        in the first time that use this app.
  -s SUBJECT, --subject=SUBJECT
                         The subject of email.

Example: python gmailcommanline.py -u greg@gmail.com -s Teste -m "Hello World!!" -d jonhdoo@anymailserver.com -a /home/greg/imagens/partytoday.png

